cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and understanding. The use of neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The task of describing a given phrase based on its context also involves information retrieval, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the use of context encoders and the creation of a new dataset from Wikipedia suggest that it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
